- A "path" in this context refers to a route in the `routes` table;
- "Footprints" are the actions (changes) recorded in the `route_history` table, including the user who made the change and the type of change.

- "High fuel consumption" is defined as an average fuel consumption greater than 10.0;
- "Anomalies" refer to issues or irregularities detected during vehicle tracking;
- "Recent route changes" are the most recent modifications to the routes, including who made the change and when.
